To further confirm the structure of the NADES-Au NCs, the surface functional groups and elemental composition information of the NADES-Au NCs were investigated by FT-IR and XPS (Fig. 2
                        ). As displayed in Fig. 2A, the full scan XPS spectrum exhibited five distinct binding energy states, where the C 1 s, N 1 s, O 1 s, Cl 2p and Au 4f signals were located at 284.8, 398.4, 530.3, 197.6, 86.6 eV, respectively. The existence of Cl and Au elements further confirmed that NADES has been successfully combined with Au NCs. As plotted in Fig. 2B, three fitted peaks of C 1 s were centered at 284.1 eV, 285.3 eV and 286.9 eV, corresponding to the binding energies of CC, CN and CO bonds respectively [29,30]. In addition, the spectrum of N 1 s was resolved, to which the high-resolution N 1 s spectrum was de-convoluted into four peaks at 398.7 eV and 401.2 eV, belonging to the NH and CN bonds, respectively (Fig. 2C) [31]. The high-resolution spectrum of O 1 s displayed two obvious peaks at 530.2 eV and 531.3 eV (Fig. 2D), which were respectively defined the CO and CO groups [32]. As shown in Fig. 4

                        E, the Au 4f XPS spectrum displayed a typical profile composed [33] of a low-energy band (Au 4f7/2) at 83.0 eV and a high-energy band (Au 4f5/2) at 86.6 eV, indicating that both Au0 and Au+ existed in the NADES-Au NCs.
